https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6750


Auth Header :
	(normal) <-----
	GET /resource HTTP/1.1
	Host: server.example.com
	Authorization: Bearer mF_9.B5f-4.1JqM

	(Form-Encoded Body Parameter)
	POST /resource HTTP/1.1
	Host: server.example.com
	Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

	access_token=mF_9.B5f-4.1JqM


	(URI Query)
	GET /resource?access_token=mF_9.B5f-4.1JqM HTTP/1.1
	Host: server.example.com


The WWW-Authenticate Response Header Field

	send it when there is a problem connecting 
		no access_token found
		toekn found but not valid 
		...

	in case of auth faillure 
		server SHOULD include the "error"


	exemple
		(no token)
		HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
		WWW-Authenticate: Bearer realm="example"

		(token invalid)
		HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
     	WWW-Authenticate: Bearer realm="example", error="invalid_token", error_description="The access token expired

    Error Codes
     	invalid_request HTTP 400 (Bad Request)
     		no token
     	invalid_token HTTP 401 (Unauthorized)
     		token provided is expired, revoked, malformed, or invalid for other reasons
     	insufficient_scope HTTP 403 (Forbidden)
     		higher privileges

     	unaware of auth HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
     		WWW-Authenticate: Bearer realm="example"


Example Access Token Response
	HTTP/1.1 200 OK
	Content-Type: application/json;charset=UTF-8
	Cache-Control: no-store
	Pragma: no-cache

	{
		"access_token":"mF_9.B5f-4.1JqM",
		"token_type":"Bearer",
		"expires_in":3600,
		"refresh_token":"tGzv3JOkF0XG5Qx2TlKWIA"
	}



Recomendation
	Don't store bearer tokens in cookies
	Issue short-lived bearer tokens (~one hour)


